A <b>faceted boolean query</b> is a query of paranthetical OR statements linked together by AND <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../153/18153.xml">
boolean operator</link>s.</p>
<p>

For example, the query (1 OR 2) AND (3 OR 4) would match any combination of either the numbers 1 or 2 and 3 or 4.  The following sets of numbers would satisfy this: [1,3], [1,4], [2,3] and [2,4].  </p>
<p>

Faceted boolean <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../390/679390.xml">
query</link>s are especially helpful in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../271/15271.xml">
information retrieval</link> such as <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../023/4059023.xml">
search engine</link> querying.  For example, the following query will return many documents on the subject of electronic voting in general: "(electronic OR computerized OR DRE) AND (voting OR elections OR election OR balloting OR electoral)" </p>

